Lagos State Commissioner for Health, Prof. Akin Abayomi has said that dump site located at Oko Filling located at Alimosho Local Government Area would soon be evacuated as early as possible, stressing that such site is danger to human health. It would be recalled that the state government through the Lagos State Waste Management Authority (LAWMA) the body entrusted with proper waste management in the state, create the landfill in solous for Material Recovery Facility (MRF) so as to sort out solid waste such as plastic bottles, cans, papers for recycling. However, the plan has not been completely executed and the community is not happy with the activities that goes on in solous dump site. Abayomi gave the promise recently, while speaking at the handing over of biomedical equipment donated to the general hospital in Igando. The equipment was donated by Medshare in collaboration with Coca-Cola company through its safe birth Initiative which is to enable mother and child get back safe and alive. According to Abayomi, the dump site “Is totally unacceptable and we are committed to completely removing it from this vicinity, the Commissioner For Environment and myself have been speaking and we have many plans even the work has started and is this time we can actually do things because when we enter the raining season it would be very difficult for us to access the dump. “We will continue because it’s going to take a few years because it took many years for that rubbish to get there and it would take many more years to get rid of it but we are on it and my commitment to you is that it is unacceptable to have a rubbish dump next to a premier general hospital in Lagos it is something we must pay attention to”. 